[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":413},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F12\u002F04\u002Fuseful-browser-extensions-for-developers\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F12\u002F04\u002Fuseful-browser-extensions-for-developers\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F12\u002F04\u002Fuseful-browser-extensions-for-developers\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F12\u002F04\u002Fuseful-browser-extensions-for-developers\u002F":388,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F12\u002F04\u002Fuseful-browser-extensions-for-developers\u002F":397},"\u002Fother\u002F20211204\u002F2579354992\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":369,"date":370,"description":371,"extension":372,"lang":373,"meta":374,"navigation":375,"path":376,"readingMinutes":377,"seo":378,"standalone":379,"stem":380,"tags":381,"tldr":385,"updated":385,"url":386,"__hash__":387},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Fuseful-browser-extensions-for-developers.md","Useful Browser Extensions for Developers","5929532497",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":354},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,35,41,44,50,53,89,92,99,106,110,113,119,125,131,135,138,144,150,153,159,163,166,172,178,184,188,191,197,203,206,212,218,224,227,231,234,240,246,252,256,259,265,271,277,281,284,290,296,302,306,309,315,321,327,331,334,339,345,351],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"There are a lot of browser extensions out there — what's worth installing if you're a developer? Quick rundown of what I personally use. I'm a Firefox primary user, so I'll list both Firefox and Chrome links where available.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"translation","Translation",[17,25,26,27,34],{},"Most Chrome users get pushed toward ",[28,29,33],"a",{"href":30,"rel":31},"https:\u002F\u002Fchrome.google.com\u002Fwebstore\u002Fdetail\u002Fgoogle-translate\u002Faapbdbdomjkkjkaonfhkkikfgjllcleb",[32],"nofollow","Google Translate",", since Google's the publisher.",[17,36,37],{},[38,39],"img",{"alt":33,"src":40},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fb74kRwy.png",[17,42,43],{},"Personally I prefer \"Saladict\" (multi-dictionary mouse-select translation):",[17,45,46],{},[38,47],{"alt":48,"src":49},"Saladict","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F1HOMoK7.png",[17,51,52],{},"It supports a stack of dictionaries:",[54,55,56,60,63,66,69,72,75,78,81,84,86],"ul",{},[57,58,59],"li",{},"Bing Dictionary",[57,61,62],{},"American Heritage Dictionary",[57,64,65],{},"Oxford Advanced Learner's Dictionary",[57,67,68],{},"Caiyun Translate",[57,70,71],{},"Cambridge Dictionary",[57,73,74],{},"CNKI Translation Assistant",[57,76,77],{},"Collins Advanced",[57,79,80],{},"Etymonline",[57,82,83],{},"Bilingual example sentences",[57,85,33],{},[57,87,88],{},"Google Dictionary",[17,90,91],{},"And more. Heads up — the dictionary coverage skews Chinese-English, so it's most useful if that pairing matters to you.",[17,93,94],{},[28,95,98],{"href":96,"rel":97},"https:\u002F\u002Fchrome.google.com\u002Fwebstore\u002Fdetail\u002F%E6%B2%99%E6%8B%89%E6%9F%A5%E8%AF%8D-%E8%81%9A%E5%90%88%E8%AF%8D%E5%85%B8%E5%88%92%E8%AF%8D%E7%BF%BB%E8%AF%91\u002Fcdonnmffkdaoajfknoeeecmchibpmkmg",[32],"Chrome download",[17,100,101],{},[28,102,105],{"href":103,"rel":104},"https:\u002F\u002Faddons.mozilla.org\u002Fen-US\u002Ffirefox\u002Faddon\u002Fext-saladict",[32],"Firefox download",[12,107,109],{"id":108},"color-picker","Color picker",[17,111,112],{},"ColorZilla is a color picker:",[17,114,115],{},[38,116],{"alt":117,"src":118},"ColorZilla","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FoGPnh4X.png",[17,120,121],{},[28,122,98],{"href":123,"rel":124},"https:\u002F\u002Fchrome.google.com\u002Fwebstore\u002Fdetail\u002Fcolorzilla\u002Fbhlhnicpbhignbdhedgjhgdocnmhomnp",[32],[17,126,127],{},[28,128,105],{"href":129,"rel":130},"https:\u002F\u002Faddons.mozilla.org\u002Fen-US\u002Ffirefox\u002Faddon\u002Fcolorzilla\u002F",[32],[12,132,134],{"id":133},"server-location","Server location",[17,136,137],{},"Flagfox shows you what country the server for the current page is in — flag of that country in the toolbar:",[17,139,140],{},[38,141],{"alt":142,"src":143},"Flagfox","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FMOFAKay.png",[17,145,146],{},[28,147,105],{"href":148,"rel":149},"https:\u002F\u002Faddons.mozilla.org\u002Fen-US\u002Ffirefox\u002Faddon\u002Fflagfox\u002F",[32],[17,151,152],{},"Chrome doesn't have Flagfox, but \"IP Domain Country Flag\" does the same thing:",[17,154,155],{},[28,156,98],{"href":157,"rel":158},"https:\u002F\u002Fchrome.google.com\u002Fwebstore\u002Fdetail\u002Fip-whois-flags-chrome-web\u002Fkmdfbacgombndnllogoijhnggalgmkon\u002Frelated",[32],[12,160,162],{"id":161},"font-identification","Font identification",[17,164,165],{},"To check what font a page is using, I'd recommend \"Fonts Ninja\":",[17,167,168],{},[38,169],{"alt":170,"src":171},"Fonts Ninja","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FVkzi2QM.png",[17,173,174],{},[28,175,105],{"href":176,"rel":177},"https:\u002F\u002Faddons.mozilla.org\u002Fen-US\u002Ffirefox\u002Faddon\u002Ffonts-ninja\u002F",[32],[17,179,180],{},[28,181,98],{"href":182,"rel":183},"https:\u002F\u002Fchrome.google.com\u002Fwebstore\u002Fdetail\u002Ffonts-ninja\u002Feljapbgkmlngdpckoiiibecpemleclhh",[32],[12,185,187],{"id":186},"tech-stack-detection","Tech stack detection",[17,189,190],{},"Wappalyzer's been around for a while — most devs have it:",[17,192,193],{},[28,194,98],{"href":195,"rel":196},"https:\u002F\u002Fchrome.google.com\u002Fwebstore\u002Fdetail\u002Fwappalyzer\u002Fgppongmhjkpfnbhagpmjfkannfbllamg",[32],[17,198,199],{},[28,200,105],{"href":201,"rel":202},"https:\u002F\u002Faddons.mozilla.org\u002Fen-US\u002Ffirefox\u002Faddon\u002Fwappalyzer\u002F",[32],[17,204,205],{},"I also use \"whatruns\" as a second opinion:",[17,207,208],{},[38,209],{"alt":210,"src":211},"whatruns","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FHQ3c5JW.png",[17,213,214],{},[28,215,98],{"href":216,"rel":217},"https:\u002F\u002Fchrome.google.com\u002Fwebstore\u002Fdetail\u002Fwhatruns\u002Fcmkdbmfndkfgebldhnkbfhlneefdaaip",[32],[17,219,220],{},[28,221,105],{"href":222,"rel":223},"https:\u002F\u002Faddons.mozilla.org\u002Fen-US\u002Ffirefox\u002Faddon\u002Fwhatruns\u002F",[32],[17,225,226],{},"For accuracy, I'd say Wappalyzer is the more reliable of the two.",[12,228,230],{"id":229},"cms-detection","CMS detection",[17,232,233],{},"For blogs and content sites, \"What CMS Is This\" tells you what CMS they're using:",[17,235,236],{},[38,237],{"alt":238,"src":239},"What CMS Is This","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FquFq3eO.png",[17,241,242],{},[28,243,98],{"href":244,"rel":245},"https:\u002F\u002Fchrome.google.com\u002Fwebstore\u002Fdetail\u002Fwhat-cms-is-this\u002Fgamohlpmdjkdjepgdgjohkbfpmeelmem",[32],[17,247,248],{},[28,249,105],{"href":250,"rel":251},"https:\u002F\u002Faddons.mozilla.org\u002Fen-US\u002Ffirefox\u002Faddon\u002Fwhat-cms-is-this",[32],[12,253,255],{"id":254},"gmail-notifications","Gmail notifications",[17,257,258],{},"\"Notifier for Gmail\" is one I really like — pings you when new mail arrives so you don't miss anything:",[17,260,261],{},[38,262],{"alt":263,"src":264},"Notifier for Gmail","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FevpSVDF.png",[17,266,267],{},[28,268,98],{"href":269,"rel":270},"https:\u002F\u002Fchrome.google.com\u002Fwebstore\u002Fdetail\u002Fnotifier-for-gmail\u002Fdcjichoefijpinlfnjghokpkojhlhkgl",[32],[17,272,273],{},[28,274,105],{"href":275,"rel":276},"https:\u002F\u002Faddons.mozilla.org\u002Fen-US\u002Ffirefox\u002Faddon\u002Fgmail-notifier-restartless\u002F",[32],[12,278,280],{"id":279},"json-viewer","JSON viewer",[17,282,283],{},"If you're a frontend dev, this one needs no explanation.",[17,285,286],{},[38,287],{"alt":288,"src":289},"JSON Viewer","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F4CFjkxZ.png",[17,291,292],{},[28,293,98],{"href":294,"rel":295},"https:\u002F\u002Fchrome.google.com\u002Fwebstore\u002Fdetail\u002Fjson-viewer\u002Fgbmdgpbipfallnflgajpaliibnhdgobh",[32],[17,297,298],{},[28,299,105],{"href":300,"rel":301},"https:\u002F\u002Faddons.mozilla.org\u002Fen-US\u002Ffirefox\u002Faddon\u002Fjsonview",[32],[12,303,305],{"id":304},"seo-analysis","SEO analysis",[17,307,308],{},"Lots of options here — I mostly use \"SEO Site Tools, Site Analysis\":",[17,310,311],{},[38,312],{"alt":313,"src":314},"SEO Site Tools","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FLiilA1i.png",[17,316,317],{},[28,318,98],{"href":319,"rel":320},"https:\u002F\u002Fchrome.google.com\u002Fwebstore\u002Fdetail\u002Fseo-site-tools-site-analy\u002Ffemogmcmjpjkokoojcljkpfdifkpbbpp",[32],[17,322,323],{},[28,324,105],{"href":325,"rel":326},"https:\u002F\u002Faddons.mozilla.org\u002Fen-US\u002Ffirefox\u002Faddon\u002Fseo-site-tools-site-analysis",[32],[12,328,330],{"id":329},"html-outliner","HTML outliner",[17,332,333],{},"Shows the full HTML hierarchy of the current page. Useful for sanity-checking your own HTML structure:",[17,335,336],{},[38,337],{"alt":330,"src":338},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FYPYExAY.png",[17,340,341],{},[28,342,98],{"href":343,"rel":344},"https:\u002F\u002Fchrome.google.com\u002Fwebstore\u002Fdetail\u002Fhtml5-outliner\u002Fafoibpobokebhgfnknfndkgemglggomo",[32],[17,346,347],{},[28,348,105],{"href":349,"rel":350},"https:\u002F\u002Faddons.mozilla.org\u002Fen-US\u002Ffirefox\u002Faddon\u002Foutline-sidebar",[32],[17,352,353],{},"That's roughly the set I use day to day.",{"title":355,"searchDepth":356,"depth":356,"links":357},"",2,[358,359,360,361,362,363,364,365,366,367,368],{"id":14,"depth":356,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":356,"text":23},{"id":108,"depth":356,"text":109},{"id":133,"depth":356,"text":134},{"id":161,"depth":356,"text":162},{"id":186,"depth":356,"text":187},{"id":229,"depth":356,"text":230},{"id":254,"depth":356,"text":255},{"id":279,"depth":356,"text":280},{"id":304,"depth":356,"text":305},{"id":329,"depth":356,"text":330},"Misc","2021-12-04 21:49:43","A quick tour of browser extensions I actually use as a developer. Covers translation, color picking (ColorZilla), server location (Flagfox \u002F IP Domain Country Flag), font identification (Fonts Ninja), tech stack detection (Wappalyzer, whatruns), CMS detection, Gmail notifications, JSON viewer, SEO analysis, and HTML outliner. Firefox-first since that's my main browser, with Chrome links where available.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002Fuseful-browser-extensions-for-developers","2",{"title":6,"description":371},false,"en\u002FMisc\u002Fuseful-browser-extensions-for-developers",[382,383,384],"Browser Extension","Chrome Extension","Firefox Extension",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F12\u002F04\u002Fuseful-browser-extensions-for-developers\u002F","aU1m2q3GxUu7LaCVqoE0mobpPTU3NXmdqqcBvgx4tMw",{"newer":389,"older":393},{"url":390,"title":391,"date":392},"\u002Fen\u002Fnuxt\u002F2021\u002F12\u002F05\u002Fnuxt-2x-handbook-05-lifecycle\u002F","Nuxt.js 2.x Hands-On Handbook (5) — Lifecycle","2021-12-05 15:18:00",{"url":394,"title":395,"date":396},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2021\u002F11\u002F28\u002Fjavascript-promise-async-await\u002F","What Is a Promise in JavaScript? And Why You Really Need to Get It","2021-11-28 16:19:37",[398,403,408],{"url":399,"title":400,"date":401,"readingMinutes":402},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F06\u002F23\u002Fmac-stats-menu-bar-system-monitor\u002F","Stats — The Free Open-Source macOS Menu Bar System Monitor I Use Every Day (CPU, GPU, Temperature, Network)","2026-06-23 10:00:00","5",{"url":404,"title":405,"date":406,"readingMinutes":407},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F26\u002Fhow-much-does-a-blog-really-earn-with-google-adsense\u002F","Can a Blog Really Make Tens of Thousands of Dollars a Month? Real Google AdSense Numbers, Explained","2026-05-26 21:00:00","6",{"url":409,"title":410,"date":411,"readingMinutes":412},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F18\u002Fvscode-disable-integrated-browser-auto-open\u002F","VSCode Opens Every Link in the Integrated Browser? How to Disable Auto Takeover","2026-05-18 14:30:00","4",1784013066156]